https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/architecture/reference-architectures/identity/

Two Solutions
  Use AD Connect to Sync On-prem objects to Cloud  (1)
  Extend your on-prem AD to Azure by running AD DS as a domain controller.
        This will reduce the network latency for sending authentication to on-prem
        Most common when you implment VPN or Express Route connection from on-prem network to Azure VNet
        Types
          Create a domain and join to onprem forest (2)
          Create forest and trusted by domains in on-premis forest (3)
          Replicate an ADFS to Azure  (4)
          
Pros and Cons
  ADConnect 
    Pros -> No need to maintain cloud infra, 
    Cons -> maintaing Sync betwen 
